        <Base:Descriptions>
          <Base:Description type="brief">
             large $(this.trait:color) $(this.trait:material) weaving loom
          </Base:Description>
          <Base:Description type="examine">
             This an 8-shaft countermarch loom, it looks slightly used. The original 8 shafts are now ground shafts, and have long-eyed heddles. The tie ups and heddles are made with a $(this.trait:cordcolor) cord. It has a hanging beater, treadles attached in the rear, and large ratchet wheels for turning the beams. The major structural elements are held in place by wedges in mortises. The loom is approximately five feet deep, the depth is sufficient to provide a better shed and lessen the strain on the warp. It also has a fabric protector. This is a thin board which is placed outside the breast beam. This allows the user to sit very close to their weaving without touching it. When raised, it prevents shuttles from falling off the loom when they are beating.
          </Base:Description>
          <Base:Description type="look">
             A large device for making blankets and clothes, with a bench beside it to sit while you work.
          </Base:Description>
        </Base:Descriptions>
