        <Base:Descriptions>
          <Base:Description type="brief">
             loom's beams
          </Base:Description>
          <Base:Description type="look">
             A stretch of wood, for the finished cloth to rest. Beater cross pieces are made from $(this.trait:material) and are designed to prevent warping or causing a crooked beat. The uprights which hold the breast beam are also $(this.trait:material) and have a bolt securing the top, as this part of the loom takes a lot of stress from warp tension. All the cross beams: the breast beam, knee beam, back beam, warp beam and cloth beam are also $(this.trait:material) and designed to hold up to warp tension. The circumference of the solid $(this.trait:material) cloth and warp beams are twelve inches.
          </Base:Description>
